ret sauce” of 52Frames.\n\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\n\nOne of the surest ways to sharpen your eye for great photography is to really <i>look</i> at a photograph, and process what works for you and what doesn’t. By taking the time to really <i>articulate</i> what you appreciate [or don’t] about a photo, you’ll force yourself to really examine the work and learn from it. At the same time, you will gain the same keen insight from the critiques of others!\n\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\n\n<i>What’s the best way?</i>\n\nThere are different philosophies on how to critique.\n\nYosef advocates the “sandwich method” in which a critique is “sandwiched” between two compliments.\n\nShai supports the “THINK method” - make sure your comment is True, Helpful, Inspiring, Necessary, and Kind.\n\n<strong>\nWhatever critique methodology you subscribe to, just make sure it comes from a place of wanting to <b>help</b> the photographer, in a <b>kind and supportive</b> way. </strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;[/vc_column_text][/vc_tab][vc_tab title=\"Project Guidelines\" tab_id=\"1419950118-2-43\"][vc_column_text]We really hate to get all rulesy, but we have a few guidelines in place to make sure our weekly challenges are fair, fun, and frickin’ fantastic. (Heads up: we adore alliteration).\n<h3><b><b>Photos Must Be Taken That Week</b></b></h3>\n&nbsp;\n\nThe goal of the project is to create a framework for you to take out your camera every single week. As such, <b>you may only submit photos you took the week of the challenge (that’s Sunday to Sunday at the deadline time - noon, (eastern U.S.)!).</b> Besides cheating yourself by submitting older photos you have on your hard drive, it’s also unfair to other participants who created something entirely new for the challenge Everyone has the same 7-day challenge; this is what makes this project work. Photographs found to be taken outside the week will be removed, and we’ll send the submitter a reminder of our guidelines (insert dramatic gong noise here!).\n<h3><b><b>Only Submit Your Own Work</b></b></h3>\n&nbsp;\n\nThis should go without saying, but we’ll say it anyway: your submissions must be your own photography. We have a zero-tolerance policy for copyright infringement and the theft of other people’s work. <b>Members found to submit other’s work will be removed from the project and forfeit any chance for prizes. They will also be solely responsible for any legal ramifications from their actions.</b> We’re not even going to write something cute here to soften the mood, because we’re so serious about this.\n<h3><b><b>Photographs, Only! And No Pictures of Pictures...</b></b></h3>\n&nbsp;\n\nWe’re a photography community, so please only submit photographs. We love that you’re exploring other media, but this community is for photographs only.\n\nSimilarly, please do not submit pictures of pictures. This is one of those “we know it when we see it situations” but some things to avoid include: a photograph of a painting (whether yours or someone elses), a computer screenshot, a photo of a TV picture or computer screen, a photo of an advertisement without any other subject or interaction in the scene. One way to think about this: if your photo isn’t copyright-able, it isn’t submit-able.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><b><b>Keep it Classy, Folks</b></b></h3>\n&nbsp;\n\nSince the camera’s invention, photographers have been depicting the beauty of the human form. Our site allows for artful nudity, and also offers a filter for users who prefer not to view it. However, images that can reasonably be considered offensive, obscene, or pornographic may not be submitted. We understand there is sometimes a fine line between the nude and the erotic, and we will trust our moderators to use their judgement in making the distinction on a case-by-case basis.\n\n&nbsp;[/vc_column_text][/vc_tab][/vc_tour][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Community Guidelines','','inherit','open','open','','551-revision-v1','','','2014-12-30 14:40:27','2014-12-30 14:40:27','',551,'http://52frames.com/551-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(555,4,'2014-12-30 14:45:03','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-30 14:45:03','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://52frames.com/?post_type=photo&p=555',0,'photo','',0),(556,4,'2014-12-30 14:45:08','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-30 14:45:08','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://52frames.com/?post_type=photo&p=556',0,'photo','',0),(557,4,'2014-12-30 14:45:10','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-30 14:45:10','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://52frames.com/?post_type=photo&p=557',0,'photo','',0),(558,4,'2014-12-30 14:47:48','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-30 14:47:48','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://52frames.com/?post_type=photo&p=558',0,'photo','',0),(559,4,'2014-12-30 15:04:19','2014-12-30 15:04:19','[vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_tour][vc_tab title=\"The Weekly Challenge\" tab_id=\"1419783734-1-37\"][vc_toggle title=\"Lemme shoot! Where do I find this week’s challenge?\" open=\"false\"]You can always find the week’s challenge on <strong>this</strong> page, along with great tips, tutorials and a look ahead at the coming week’s challenges. Bookmark it for easy access!\r\n\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"What’s this “Extra Credit” thing all about?\" open=\"false\"]We\'re excited to introduce the \"Extra Credit\" Challenge. Every week we\'ll offer a small twist for more ambitious photographers who want some direction in pushing themselves just a bit harder. Each week, you can decide to take it on, or not. It\'s extra credit!\r\n\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"I got my shot! Where do I submit my photo?\" open=\"false\"]Make sure you have an account and that you’re logged in. Then simply go to the submission form, upload your photo, check the appropriate boxes, and submit!\r\n\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"I submitted my photo, but I don’t see it on the site! \" open=\"false\"]Your photos aren’t immediately visible. Once the week’s deadline hits (that’s every Sunday at noon, Eastern U.S. time), our panel of judges select the week’s winners, and then publish the album. This may take a few hours, but we’ll make an announcement on our Facebook page once the album is live! (So make sure you’ve ‘liked’ our page!).\r\n\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"How are the winners chosen?\" open=\"false\"]Bribery, pure and simple. (We kid, we kid.)\r\n\r\nWe take the judging very seriously (which, incidentally, is sometimes why there are delays posting the album). We invite expert photographers to help us select the best photographs each week. We consider storytelling, technique, creativity, and the connection between the photo and the week’s challenge. Sometimes we see a fantastic photo that feels like a “shoe-horn” (that’s what we call a photo that doesn’t reeeeally fit the theme), which is ok as a submission, but not for an award.\r\n\r\nArt is necessarily a subjective experience, so we try to assemble a panel of judges with different styles, tastes and preferences. Some of the most spirited arguments we’ve ever had were focused on which photograph should “win” a challenge. But we’re still friends.[/vc_toggle][/vc_tab][vc_tab title=\"The Rules\" tab_id=\"1419783734-2-51\"][vc_toggle title=\"I sure would love to see a page of the community guidelines, and rules. Where can I find such a thing?\" open=\"false\"]That wasn’t at all a contrived question that we had our fictional questioner pose! In fact, we do have such a page. <a title=\"Community Guidelines\" href=\"http://52frames.com/members/community-guidelines/\">Over here</a>.\r\n\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"I have a great photo in my archive that’s PERFECT for this week. Can I submit it?\" open=\"false\"]No. You may ONLY submit a photo that was taken taken during the week of the present challenge. You are, however, welcome to share your photo goodnesses in our <a href=\"facebook.com/groups/52fadmin/\" target=\"_blank\">52Frames Photographers’ Facebook group</a> to inspire the community.\r\n\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Can I submit a photo that was shot just a few hours before last week’s deadline?\" open=\"false\"]No. The 52Frames project is a 7-day challenge, so push yourself to get one really creative and inventive shot, each week. The clock starts at 12:01pm, each Sunday, Eastern U.S. time, and ends at noon, the following week.\r\n\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Can I change my photo (or photo details) once I’ve submitted?\" open=\"false\"]Yes. (See? It’s not all “no”s).  Simply go to your photo page, and replace your photo with the new one. You’ll also be able to edit any information you put in for that photo.\r\n\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"When is the deadline for the weekly challenge?\" open=\"false\"]The deadline each week is noon (12:00pm) Eastern U.S. time. (When in doubt, just google: “What time is it in New York”). We’ll wave our hands wildly in the air when we know about the clock being changed in different countries, but your best bet is simply not to wait until the last minute.\r\n\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"If I miss a week, am I allowed to continue the project?\" open=\"false\"]Yes! But you will no longer be considered a “Weekly Warrior” (name pending), and you won’t be eligible for any badges or contests associated with it. While a successful 52-week run is ideal, we understand that life sometimes gets in the way, and it’s more important to just have fun, and post when you can! We believe consistency is the most important thing, so go ahead and submit a photo even if you’re not crazy about it! We’ll understand. (Also, some of the best shots we’ve seen were submitted by completely unenthusiastic members just trying to stay “consistent”).\r\n\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Can I submit a photo after the deadline?\" open=\"false\"]No. The deadline is a HARD deadline, like a turtle shell, or umm, a very stale piece of bread. Any submission sent in after Sunday at noon Eastern U.S., will NOT be accepted for that week’s album.\r\n\r\n[/vc_toggle][/vc_tab][vc_tab title=\"Other Questions\" tab_id=\"1419783849818-2-0\"][vc_toggle title=\"I have a tech-related problem, like I’m having trouble submitting my photo, or there’s something wrong with the site. Whom do I contact?\" open=\"false\"]Let us know! Send an email to <a href=\"mailto:help@52frames.com\">help@52frames.com</a>, or ask a question on the <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/groups/52fadmin/\" target=\"_blank\">52Frames Photographers’ Facebook group</a>.[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"I want to meet you. Do you have regular meetups “in real life”?\" open=\"false\"]Yes! 52Frames runs monthly “Photowalks” in different cities around the world. Check out our Photowalks page to find out if a photowalk is happening in your area, they are great fun.\r\n\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"I have a question that’s not on here, whom do I ask?\" open=\"false\"]If you’re not already in our <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/groups/52fadmin/\" target=\"_blank\">52Frames Photographers’ Facebook group</a>, check it out and ask your question there, we’re a very helpful community. You can also email us at <a href=\"mailto:help@52frames.com\">help@52frames.com</a> if you’re having other trouble.\r\n\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"How do I sign up for the monthly newsletter?\" open=\"false\"]<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/52frames/app_100265896690345\" target=\"_blank\">Here!</a>[/vc_toggle][/vc_tab][/vc_tour][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Member\'s FAQ','','publish','open','open','','members-faq','','','2014-12-30 15:37:57','2014-12-30 15:37:57','',239,'http://52frames.com/?page_id=559',0,'page','',0),(560,4,'2014-12-30 15:04:19','2014-12-30 15:04:19','[vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_tour][vc_tab title=\"The Weekly Chal