n-Rave-Self-Portrait-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> Photo Credit: Nomi Hirshman-Rave Week 1 (2014) : Self-Portrait[/caption]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Country: United States</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Joined 52Frames: January, 2014</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Favorite color - I like them all</p>','Featured Framer: Nomi Hirshman-Rave','','inherit','open','open','','870-revision-v1','','','2014-12-31 11:37:52','2014-12-31 11:37:52','',870,'http://52frames.com/blog/uncategorized/870-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(911,4,'2014-12-31 11:40:31','2014-12-31 11:40:31','[caption id=\"attachment_878\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://52frames.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Nomi-Hirshman-Rave-Self-Portrait.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-878\" src=\"http://52frames.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Nomi-Hirshman-Rave-Self-Portrait-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> Photo Credit: Nomi Hirshman-Rave Week 1 (2014) : Self-Portrait[/caption]\r\n\r\nCountry: United States\r\n\r\nJoined 52Frames: January, 2014\r\n\r\nFavorite color - I like them all\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>What makes you passionate about photography?</h2>\r\nFor me it’s a blank canvas, it’s my Art Therapy, I see the progress, I feel accomplished, and there is no limit to what I can do.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\nWho’s photography most inspires you in 52Frames and why?\r\n\r\nRudi Bishop - Because his shoots are amazing and they tell a story. His post processing is unbelievable and he always clearly shares how he shoots, I feel I can learn a lot from him.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\nKái Jài - He is so creative and I love his use of colors.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\nNechama Leitner - Because she improves so much with every submission. I just can’t wait to see her next shot to see how she’s improved.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\nVitri Balram - Because her shoots are so romantic and focused. I always see her photos with such clarity.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\nWho is your favorite historical or modern photographer, and why?\r\n\r\nRafi Koren - he is an inspiration to success and because he is a great teacher and mentor.\r\n\r\nKaterina Irlin - her NYC photography is an inspiration and I know her personally, from even before she was a successful photographer.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\nWhat’s in your camera bag?\r\n\r\nFujifilm X-e2\r\n\r\n35mm\r\n\r\n18-55mm\r\n\r\na few filters\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\nWhat’s the last great tip you learned?\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\nReset your camera to these settings every night!\r\n\r\nISO200\r\n\r\nf5.6\r\n\r\n1/125sec\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\nWhat are your 3 favorite shots you’ve submitted to 52Frames? What makes them your favorite?\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\nWeek 47 (2014): Portrait -\r\n\r\nThis was my 3rd click on my new 35mm lens and I love how it came out and I won the cover with it!\r\n\r\nhttps://www.dropbox.com/s/k3hze7a70o2wwi0/243-%20Nomi%20Hirshman-Rave%20-%20portrait%20USE%20THIS%20ONE.jpg?dl=0\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\nWeek 50 (2014): Contrast\r\n\r\nThis was my first time I shot with a professional model. I took two risks:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The location was a “No Photography” area so we had to shoot it very fast.</li>\r\n	<li>I was shooting at f1.4, and the image came out very focused and very strong because of it.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nhttps://www.dropbox.com/s/s5syonwy4zbb1an/243-%20Nomi%20Hirshman-Rave%20-%20Contrast.jpg?dl=0\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\nWeek 17 (2014): Focus\r\n\r\nThis was one of my first shots with my new Fujifilm camera and my first time post processing ‘tilt shift’ and I love how it turned out.\r\n\r\nhttps://www.dropbox.com/s/5kutgddlqo56doa/243%20-%20Nomi%20Hirshman-Rave%20-Focus%20FINAL%21%21.jpg?dl=0\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\nWhat advice would you give someone just starting out in photography?\r\n\r\nSearch for photographers online and follow the ones that inspire you. Try and connect to one or two mentors that can teach you and give you honest and supportive feedback. Read up about exposure and post processing and experiment by trying to emulate shots of your favorite photographers. This experiential learning will help you find your own way, quickly.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><strong>\r\n\r\n</strong></strong></p>\r\nWould you like to nominate a Framer to be featured? Let us know: <a href=\"mailto:info@52frames.com\">info@52frames.com</a> (subject: Nominate Featured Framer)\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>\r\n&nbsp;','Featured Framer: Nomi Hirshman-Rave','','inherit','open','open','','870-revision-v1','','','2014-12-31 11:40:31','2014-12-31 11:40:31','',870,'http://52frames.com/blog/uncategorized/870-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(912,4,'2014-12-31 11:46:26','2014-12-31 11:46:26','[caption id=\"attachment_878\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://52frames.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Nomi-Hirshman-Rave-Self-Portrait.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-878\" src=\"http://52frames.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Nomi-Hirshman-Rave-Self-Portrait-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> Photo Credit: Nomi Hirshman-Rave Week 1 (2014) : Self-Portrait[/caption]\r\n\r\nCountry: United States\r\n\r\nJoined 52Frames: January, 2014\r\n\r\nFavorite color - I like them all\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Wh